main event: A gray metallic object, estimated to be 50 feet from the observer and traveling approximately 70 mph, was sighted and photographed in King of Prussia, Pennsylvania on February 13, 1967.
interesting points: The observer sighted and photographed the object for 33 seconds.
The object was described as a gray metallic object, traveling in a straight course.
No photograph of the object was included in the report, but the observer requested to have their picture back.
The observer completed a questionnaire about the sighting on April 23, 1967.
The report indicates that the object was likely a reflection or other misidentification, as the photographic image was blurred and unfocused.
photographs: Yes, but not included in the report
